The paper deals with the use of OWL, a Web Ontology Language, as an answer set programming (ASP) language. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses reasoning tasks such as satisfiability and axiom entailment, which are related to databases (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a translation into ASP, which is a form of logic programming (cs.PL).
